timeline.bodyText:
I'd rather resolve return value if the handler is of type Void. In other situations, it's fine to return null:
@CommandHandler
public MySuperAwesomeReturnType handle(MyCommand cmd) {
  if (iDontLikeMyCmd(cmd)) {
    return null;
  }
  return nonNullValue;
}

